{"TopicId":139356,"ForumId":69,"TopicTitle":"Ladder switching in 1.1\u002B","CreatedByName":"Fwiffo","CreatedById":148084,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-09T02:11:54Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Fwiffo","CreatedById":148084,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-09T02:11:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGetting kerbals who are in EVA to switch between two ladders \u003Ca href=\u0022https://webcache.googleusercontent.com/search?q=cache:RYkALxBDRGAJ:forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php%3F/topic/136486-transitioning-between-perpendicular-ladders/\u002B\u0026amp;cd=3\u0026amp;hl=en\u0026amp;ct=clnk\u0026amp;gl=ca\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Egot harder\u003C/a\u003E in 1.1 / 1.1.1 /\u00A01.1.2. \u00A0Here\u0027s the \u003Ca href=\u0022http://bugs.kerbalspaceprogram.com/issues/8715\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ebug report\u003C/a\u003E, so I\u0027m not posting more details here (but can if needed).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m wondering if anyone has tips they\u0027ve discovered for mitigating this, e.g. how to line up two perpendicular ladders in a manner that makes the transition more reliable, use of \u003Ca href=\u0022http://bugs.kerbalspaceprogram.com/attachments/16261/screenshot15.png\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E45 degree connectors\u003C/a\u003E, etc.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-05-09T02:15:08Z\u0022 title=\u002205/09/2016 02:15  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EMay 9, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Fwiffo\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"bewing","CreatedById":154251,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-09T02:35:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn our testing on that bug, Anquietas said that it was fairly easy to get the 45 degree connectors working (or, I assume, anything less than 45 degrees). I never bothered to test the 45 degree ones. And as I said on the bug report, I disagree with sal_vager\u0027s wording. It didn\u0027t just \u0022get harder\u0022 to turn 90 degrees\u00A0-- it\u0027s basically impossible.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Fwiffo","CreatedById":148084,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-09T04:45:59Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks. \u00A0I\u0027ve been trying 45 degree connectors, the kerbals still seem to get confused more often than not as to which way I want them to go, at least\u00A0when the connectors aren\u0027t placed at the ends of the ladder.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sal_vager","CreatedById":16426,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-09T09:29:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTry not to place ladders too close together, as that confuses the game as to which collider you\u0027re closest to.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Fwiffo","CreatedById":148084,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-11T17:35:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222570529\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022139356\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221462786155\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002216426\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022sal_vager\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 5/9/2016 at 5:29 AM, sal_vager said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTry not to place ladders too close together\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAt the ends, that\u0027s fine. \u00A0But when you want to make two ladders abut each other in the middle of one, you need to have some overlap. \u00A0Below is an example someone was kind enough to screenshot. \u00A0What I\u0027m finding in situations like this is, climbing toward the main segment works fine. \u00A0But when you start from the bottom, climb\u00A0\u003Cem\u003Eup \u003C/em\u003Ethe main section\u00A0and you get to the Y, the game gets confused whether you want to continue straight up or turn off.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022screenshot15.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022562\u0022 src=\u0022http://bugs.kerbalspaceprogram.com/attachments/16261/screenshot15.png\u0022 width=\u00221000\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHere\u0027s my craft file, maybe a kind soul here will have better luck than me making my ladders all connect seamlessly :-).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://tinyurl.com/Rig-Mk2-PreweldC\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://tinyurl.com/Rig-Mk2-PreweldC\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022QiAkPAP.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022750\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/QiAkPAP.png\u0022 width=\u0022795\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLet me know if there are any other custom parts I forgot to include and I\u0027ll provide them. \u00A0If you need to move around heavier parts, keep in mind that I need to maintain craft balance\u00A0along two axis (center stack mounted during launch/interplanetary, and via the 4 thuds during landing / suborbital hop. \u00A0Note the terrier is temporary to have a thrust pivot point for RCS Build Aid tweaking).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMy current attempt is to make a big serpentine \u0022S\u0022 path to remove T / Y joints altogether, but it\u0027s uglier than the nice clean 90-degrees connections we had in earlier versions.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-05-11T18:39:29Z\u0022 title=\u002205/11/2016 06:39  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EMay 11, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Fwiffo\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003ESecond pic\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sal_vager","CreatedById":16426,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-11T17:40:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222575471\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022139356\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221462988103\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022148084\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Fwiffo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 minutes ago, Fwiffo said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents ipsClearfix\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAt the ends, that\u0027s fine. \u00A0But when you want to make two ladders abut each other in the middle of one, you need to have some overlap.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat looks a lot like my tests as well.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Fwiffo","CreatedById":148084,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-11T17:41:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022http://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/16426-sal_vager/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002216426\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/16426-sal_vager/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@sal_vager\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0Oh, that\u0027s your screenshot isn\u0027t it! Thanks :-)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-05-11T18:20:42Z\u0022 title=\u002205/11/2016 06:20  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EMay 11, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Fwiffo\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Fwiffo","CreatedById":148084,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-13T00:31:48Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022http://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/16426-sal_vager/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002216426\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/16426-sal_vager/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@sal_vager\u003C/a\u003E, \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022http://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/154251-bewing/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022154251\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/154251-bewing/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@bewing\u003C/a\u003E, and whoever else might stumble across similar difficulties in the future.\u00A0 After an infuriating amount of\u00A0tweaking I finally managed to get my ladders to work reliably enough by getting rid of all the junctions and following a serpentine pattern:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u00225uWYIUJ.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022750\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/5uWYIUJ.png\u0022 width=\u0022775\u0022\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#A9A9A9;\u0022\u003E\u003Cem\u003E(ignore the Poodle engines, they\u0027re just there to help with balancing in the editor)\u003C/em\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s a shame as I might have wanted to stack additional parts onto the ore holding tanks and\u00A0extend the longitudinal ladder segments along the rest of my ship.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso, unfortunately due to the asymmetries the \u0022S\u0022 approach\u00A0introduced, a downside is that\u00A0I had to resort to some silly looking weldments (or subassemblies, whatever approach you prefer) in order to avoid having to increase the number of distinct \u0022drop in segments\u0022 required for my craft:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022bxSi6RD.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/bxSi6RD.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m mentioning it to show that the ladder thing really is causing my kerbgineers\u00A0a bit of grief beyond just having to play with angles on parts.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:18px;\u0022\u003E\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022http://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/66485-squad/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002266485\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/66485-squad/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@SQUAD\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0please show bug \u003Ca href=\u0022http://bugs.kerbalspaceprogram.com/issues/8715\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E#8715\u003C/a\u003E some love and give us back reliable perpendicular ladder handoff!\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-05-13T00:44:16Z\u0022 title=\u002205/13/2016 12:44  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EMay 13, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Fwiffo\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sal_vager","CreatedById":16426,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-13T09:35:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022http://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/148084-fwiffo/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022148084\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/148084-fwiffo/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Fwiffo\u003C/a\u003E, have you considered using the retractable ladders as a switchable junction?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Fwiffo","CreatedById":148084,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-13T09:40:49Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222578971\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022139356\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221463132111\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002216426\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022sal_vager\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 minutes ago, sal_vager said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nhave you considered using the retractable ladders as switchable junction?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI hadn\u0027t; that\u0027s an interesting idea. \u00A0I think I follow what you mean, but do you have an example handy?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sal_vager","CreatedById":16426,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-13T10:02:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOne sec I\u0027ll make a pic.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022http://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/148084-fwiffo/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022148084\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/148084-fwiffo/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Fwiffo\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ciframe class=\u0022imgur-album\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022550\u0022 src=\u0022//imgur.com/a/dZMGn/embed?background=ffffff\u0026amp;text=1a1a1a\u0026amp;link=4e76c9\u0022 width=\u0022100%\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Fwiffo","CreatedById":148084,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-13T10:53:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222578997\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022139356\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221463133771\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002216426\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022sal_vager\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n55 minutes ago, sal_vager said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOne sec I\u0027ll make a pic.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks! \u00A0It\u0027s a clever idea, although\u00A0from the screenshots it seems that the junction does still need to be at the ends of the ladders rather than meeting in the middle of one (such as the way I was trying to connect to the research lab). \u00A0That said, it does eliminate the issue of kerbals getting confused at junctions, and it\u0027s great to have another tool in my toolbox. \u00A0\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#A9A9A9;\u0022\u003E\u003Cem\u003EChoo choo, chugga chugga chugga here comes the Kerbal!\u003C/em\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-05-13T10:58:48Z\u0022 title=\u002205/13/2016 10:58  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EMay 13, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Fwiffo\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"}]}